node.text: No loyalty when big money is involved. So many overpayments that will need to be bought out or traded away in a few years. Landeskog, Barrie, Ceci, Danault, Grubauer, Coleman, Schwartz, Goodrow, Suter (again lmfao), Jones, Hamilton contracts are among a few that will not age well...

node.text: What the actual fuck is Carolina doing this offseason

node.text: THAT'S how Vegas treats their franchise goaltender after winning the Vezina this year? Holy shit I knew they were cold blooded but not even telling him and letting him find out via Twitter

node.text: Voracek will be a better playmaker for Laine with one less year on his contract but damn Cam was committed to CBJ for life, you gotta feel for jackets fans right now

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Original Hockey Memes 🇺🇲 on July 24, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and text that says 'Landeskog and Makar demanding $9M+ MacKinnon taking ahuge pay cut to keep the team together @blind_ ref logic'.

node.text: Makar signs at $9Mx6. It would be an insult to give MacKinnon any less on his next contract...things aren't looking good for Colorado. If they can't win with this core now it's game over man
